videos.description: Noah Dickerson makes an easy layup after a great dime from David Crisp.
videos.headline: UW's Crisp goes around defender with pass

videos.description: Mitch Lightfoot throws it down for the Jayhawks right on a Washington defender.
videos.headline: Lightfoot puts defender on a poster

videos.description: Sam Timmins takes a foul but still finishes with a dunk for Washington.
videos.headline: Timmins throws it down with the foul

videos.description: Devonte' Graham puts the Jayhawks in the lead after a 3-pointer well behind the line.
videos.headline: Graham knocks down deep 3-pointer

videos.description: Sam Timmins ends up open behind the defense and finishes with an alley-oop for Washington.
videos.headline: Timmins left alone for alley-oop

videos.description: Lagerald Vick gets a huge and-1 for the Jayhawks as they trail the Huskies in the second half.
videos.headline: Vick takes contact but gets the and-1 to go

videos.description: Matisse Thybulle reads the pass and takes it the other way for a breakaway slam.
videos.headline: Thybulle comes up with a steal and a jam

videos.description: David Crisp knocks down a huge 3-pointer to put Washington up 14 on Kansas.
videos.headline: Crisp puts the dagger in KU

videos.description: Mike Hopkins and his Huskies pull off the biggest upset of the season entering the game with a 3.2 percent chance to win, defeating Kansas.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCB Interview (Huskies Mike Hopkins join SC to discuss big upset over KU) 12/06/2017 ESHEET SC

videos.headline: Huskies Mike Hopkins join SC to discuss big upset over KU

videos.description: After Kansas' loss to unranked Washington, Bill Self says he could see this loss coming because his team isn't "extremely quick and not very big." Self admits that if his guys aren't going to play with a chip on their shoulder, they're going to lose.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCB Press Conference (Self: 'We deserved exactly what we got tonight') 2017/12/6

videos.headline: Self: 'We deserved exactly what we got tonight'
